## Tool Framework

1. Purpose

   - Support development workflow
   - Provide utility scripts
   - Configure development tools
   - Enable project tooling

2. Organization

   - .workspace/scripts/: Development automation (assistant-agnostic)
   - .workspace/config/: Tool configurations shared across assistants
   - Assistant-specific tools/config remain in their directories (e.g., `.cursor/`, `.claude/`)

3. Best Practices
   - Put shared project scripts in `.workspace/scripts/` and configs in `.workspace/config/`
   - Keep assistant-specific rules/configuration in their respective directories
   - Document tool usage in `.workspace/docs/` and reference from assistant-specific docs
   - Maintain independence between shared scripts and assistant-specific layers
